---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Research"
  description="Research interests for Hexin Yu, including aviation network resilience, delay propagation, regional airport performance, GIS, and transportation systems."
>
  <div class="page-shell">
    <header class="container page-intro">
      <p class="page-kicker">Research</p>
      <h1>Reading aviation systems through data and geography</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        My current interests center on the shape of delay: where disruptions begin, how they travel,
        and what airport networks reveal when they are studied as geographic systems.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="container research-list" aria-label="Research interests">
      <article>
        <h2>Current Interests</h2>
        <p>
          Aviation analytics, public transportation datasets, geospatial visualization, route-level risk,
          and data tools that help explain complex systems without hiding their uncertainty.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Hub vs Regional Airport Performance</h2>
        <p>
          Comparing how large hub airports and smaller regional airports absorb, amplify, or inherit operational
          disruptions across different route structures.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Delay Propagation Across Airline Networks</h2>
        <p>
          Studying how late aircraft, congested airports, and tight schedule dependencies can turn local delays
          into wider network effects.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Aviation Network Resilience</h2>
        <p>
          Asking what makes a route system recoverable: redundancy, geography, airport capacity, carrier strategy,
          and the ability to reroute passengers and aircraft.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>GIS and Transportation Systems</h2>
        <p>
          Building maps and visual interfaces that connect route networks, airport regions, and operational
          patterns in ways that support careful interpretation.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h2>Future Directions</h2>
        <p>
          Future work may connect live aviation data, historical reliability, weather context, and airport network
          structure into lightweight decision-support tools for route risk exploration.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .research-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .research-list article {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(220px, 0.36fr) minmax(0, 0.64fr);
    gap: 36px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72), transparent);
    padding: 28px 0;
  }

  .research-list p {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .research-list article {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 10px;
    }
  }
</style>
